  "prompt": "What are the top 4 Common features for E-commerce software?",
  "response": "E-commerce software typically includes a variety of features to facilitate online selling and improve the user experience. The top four common features include:\n\n1. **Product Management**:\n   - This feature allows businesses to add, edit, and organize their products effectively. It often includes options for setting prices, managing inventory, categorizing products, and adding product descriptions, images, and specifications.\n\n2. **Shopping Cart and Checkout Process**:\n   - A user-friendly shopping cart allows customers to add products, review their selections, and proceed to a streamlined checkout process. This feature may include guest checkout options, multiple payment methods (credit cards, digital wallets, etc.), and a responsive design for mobile devices.\n\n3. **Payment Processing**:\n   - E-commerce software typically integrates with various payment gateways to securely handle transactions. This feature includes support for credit and debit card processing, electronic wallets (like PayPal and Stripe), and other payment options, ensuring customer data security and compliance with relevant regulations.\n\n4. **Order Management and Fulfillment**:\n   - Efficient order management features help track customer orders from placement to delivery. This includes order tracking, status updates, inventory management, and integration with shipping carriers for real-time shipping rates and label printing.\n\nThese features work together to create a comprehensive e-commerce experience that enhances customer satisfaction and streamlines business operations.",
